00:33:10,419 --> 00:33:12,679
The partners have come to
a unanimous decision...

530
00:33:13,279 --> 00:33:15,238
to elect Jang Hae Kyung...

531
00:33:15,239 --> 00:33:18,549
as the new managing partner of Geum San.

532
00:33:27,549 --> 00:33:28,549
Thank you.

533
00:33:29,279 --> 00:33:31,128
Geum San will no longer be...

534
00:33:31,129 --> 00:33:34,019
a law firm which speaks only
for large corporations,

535
00:33:34,349 --> 00:33:37,319
but a firm that takes the side of
the weak, who need legal services.

536
00:33:37,779 --> 00:33:41,819
We must become a law firm
loved by the people.

537
00:33:42,319 --> 00:33:43,349
I also believe...

538
00:33:43,719 --> 00:33:46,718
you should become people of
the law who value ethics...

539
00:33:46,719 --> 00:33:48,688
and be reborn as such.

540
00:33:48,689 --> 00:33:50,149
(Managing Partner, Jang Hae Kyung)

541
00:34:01,249 --> 00:34:02,249
I...

542
00:34:02,679 --> 00:34:03,679
Ma'am.

543
00:34:04,219 --> 00:34:05,449
I'm sorry for everything.

544
00:34:06,349 --> 00:34:07,779
Geum San will change.

545
00:34:08,649 --> 00:34:09,649
So,

546
00:34:10,749 --> 00:34:12,419
you'll need to help.

547
00:34:15,949 --> 00:34:17,958
I'll work hard with a new heart.

548
00:34:17,959 --> 00:34:20,519
Ask anything. I'll do my best.

549
00:34:22,049 --> 00:34:23,049
Please,

550
00:34:28,649 --> 00:34:29,649
leave Geum San.

551
00:34:31,479 --> 00:34:32,479
What was that?

552
00:34:36,749 --> 00:34:38,179
Are you kicking me out?

553
00:34:38,749 --> 00:34:41,438
I played a part in making
Geum San what it is today.

554
00:34:41,439 --> 00:34:42,908
Do you think I'll leave voluntarily?

555
00:34:42,909 --> 00:34:44,509
I'm not asking you to leave voluntarily.

556
00:34:44,949 --> 00:34:45,979
Kim Tae Jung,

557
00:34:46,419 --> 00:34:47,419
you're fired.

558
00:34:49,779 --> 00:34:50,779
Ma'am.

559
00:34:51,119 --> 00:34:53,679
You want to fire people
at your whim, is that it?

560
00:34:54,349 --> 00:34:55,979
This is a violation of the labour law!

561
00:34:58,419 --> 00:35:00,519
Labour law? Give me a break.

562
00:35:01,349 --> 00:35:03,878
It's natural that she
fire a criminal like you.

563
00:35:03,879 --> 00:35:05,949
Watch your mouth! What
do you mean, a criminal?

564
00:35:06,719 --> 00:35:07,719
Kim Tae Jung.

565
00:35:08,619 --> 00:35:10,249
I have a gift for you.

566
00:35:11,649 --> 00:35:13,149
Gosh.

567
00:35:15,179 --> 00:35:16,179
Do you remember this?

568
00:35:17,419 --> 00:35:20,248
The USB drive that you hired
someone to steal from my office.

569
00:35:20,249 --> 00:35:21,949
I suffered quite a bit because of this.

570
00:35:31,019 --> 00:35:32,549
I don't know what that is.

571
00:35:32,919 --> 00:35:34,149
I saw you pay...

572
00:35:34,549 --> 00:35:36,119
your supposed friend for that.

573
00:35:47,319 --> 00:35:48,389
We have a witness, too.

574
00:35:49,219 --> 00:35:50,948
Inciting burglary.

575
00:35:50,949 --> 00:35:53,389
Money-laundering Daehwa Group's
slush fund is an added bonus.

576
00:35:53,919 --> 00:35:55,799
Is that sufficient grounds
for termination now?

577
00:35:58,579 --> 00:36:00,419
I've made plenty of copies,

578
00:36:01,049 --> 00:36:02,319
so don't get any stupid ideas.

579
00:36:19,279 --> 00:36:21,219
Why are you giving that
to me behind your back?

580
00:36:22,719 --> 00:36:23,918
I wanted...

581
00:36:23,919 --> 00:36:25,679
to get you cookies or something,

582
00:36:26,179 --> 00:36:27,819
but she said I needed to bring you these.

583
00:36:33,119 --> 00:36:35,568
Congratulations on becoming
the managing partner.

584
00:36:35,569 --> 00:36:36,579
It suits you.

585
00:36:37,479 --> 00:36:38,479
Thanks.

586
00:36:38,919 --> 00:36:40,768
Enjoy your time together.

587
00:36:40,769 --> 00:36:41,938
I'll leave you two alone.

588
00:36:41,939 --> 00:36:43,719
And congratulations.

589
00:36:44,579 --> 00:36:45,649
Where are you going?

590
00:36:48,549 --> 00:36:50,549
You can't even eat that.

591
00:36:53,219 --> 00:36:54,219
Thanks.

592
00:36:56,579 --> 00:36:57,979
If it weren't for you,

593
00:36:59,149 --> 00:37:00,179
I never could've done it.

594
00:37:02,349 --> 00:37:04,979
Your name was outside on your door.

595
00:37:05,519 --> 00:37:06,519
It looked good.

596
00:37:08,749 --> 00:37:10,179
I'm going to visit my dad.

597
00:37:10,649 --> 00:37:11,649
Will you come with me?

598
00:37:13,149 --> 00:37:14,149
Sure.

599
00:37:40,819 --> 00:37:43,119
How is your health? Are you doing okay?

600
00:37:43,719 --> 00:37:44,749
Yes.

601
00:37:45,579 --> 00:37:47,858
Since I no longer drink
and exercise regularly,

602
00:37:47,859 --> 00:37:49,418
I've been well.

603
00:37:49,419 --> 00:37:50,549
I'm glad to hear that.

604
00:37:52,579 --> 00:37:53,749
Hae Kyung...

605
00:37:54,979 --> 00:37:57,219
was appointed as the managing
partner at Geum San today.

606
00:37:59,719 --> 00:38:01,949
Congratulations, Ms Jang.

607
00:38:04,049 --> 00:38:05,319
Hae Kyung plans...

608
00:38:06,389 --> 00:38:08,319
to change Geum San from now on.

609
00:38:09,619 --> 00:38:12,679
That is up to Ms Jang.

610
00:38:14,719 --> 00:38:16,049
And Mr Shin...

611
00:38:16,889 --> 00:38:18,219
has been arrested.

612
00:38:20,349 --> 00:38:21,479
I heard about that.

613
00:38:25,049 --> 00:38:26,519
Please take a good care of...

614
00:38:27,619 --> 00:38:29,019
Hae Kyung.

615
00:38:30,019 --> 00:38:31,179
Don't worry, Sir.

616
00:38:31,889 --> 00:38:33,579
If you're planning to get back together,

617
00:38:34,619 --> 00:38:36,389
do so while I'm in here.

618
00:38:37,319 --> 00:38:39,279
I may not approve of it once I'm out.

619
00:38:44,619 --> 00:38:45,679
There's no need.

620
00:38:47,649 --> 00:38:50,349
We'd like to stay as friends as we are now.

621
00:38:55,649 --> 00:38:58,249
I feel like fighting against
loneliness with a glass of alcohol.

622
00:38:58,719 --> 00:39:02,049
- Ta-da!
- What is it?

623
00:39:02,649 --> 00:39:06,008
You need to put this on your face.

624
00:39:06,009 --> 00:39:07,949
There's plenty of serum on this face mask.

625
00:39:09,419 --> 00:39:11,679
You need to keep caring for your skin...

626
00:39:12,119 --> 00:39:13,908
so that Dae Soo will like you.

627
00:39:13,909 --> 00:39:15,668
Why would I do this for Dae Soo?

628
00:39:15,669 --> 00:39:17,138
I'll do it for my own sake.

629
00:39:17,139 --> 00:39:19,738
Besides, there's nothing
between me and Dae Soo.

630
00:39:19,739 --> 00:39:21,019
What do you mean?

631
00:39:21,349 --> 00:39:22,919
I know everything about...

632
00:39:23,319 --> 00:39:24,549
you two.

633
00:39:24,949 --> 00:39:26,588
Goodness. Don't be ridiculous.

634
00:39:26,589 --> 00:39:28,638
I don't think you know what's going on.

635
00:39:28,639 --> 00:39:30,538
When there's no one else in the office,

636
00:39:30,539 --> 00:39:33,498
he flirts with me like a peacock.

637
00:39:33,499 --> 00:39:35,508
Besides, why would I
meet such an old geezer?

638
00:39:35,509 --> 00:39:37,008
I like someone else.

639
00:39:37,009 --> 00:39:38,849
I like Song Joong Ki.

640
00:39:39,579 --> 00:39:40,798
Is that so?

641
00:39:40,799 --> 00:39:43,889
- I find Mr Shin amazing.
- What about him?

642
00:39:44,549 --> 00:39:46,258
I get that he's a prosecutor,

643
00:39:46,259 --> 00:39:49,319
but it must be distressing
to prosecute his own father.

644
00:39:50,179 --> 00:39:53,019
- Why are you worried about Mr Shin?
- What?

645
00:39:53,819 --> 00:39:55,258
Now that I think about it,

646
00:39:55,259 --> 00:39:58,279
- you two look great together.
- What?

647
00:39:58,719 --> 00:40:00,098
Is there something going
on between you two?

648
00:40:00,099 --> 00:40:01,649
What on earth are you talking about?

649
00:40:02,049 --> 00:40:03,298
We just met...

650
00:40:03,299 --> 00:40:06,328
as an attorney and a prosecutor
at court a few times.

651
00:40:06,329 --> 00:40:07,908
We had drinks a couple of times.
That's all.

652
00:40:07,909 --> 00:40:10,708
You had drinks with him? That says it all.

653
00:40:10,709 --> 00:40:12,308
Gosh, there's nothing going on.

654
00:40:12,309 --> 00:40:14,579
What do you mean, nothing?
There's definitely something.

655
00:40:14,979 --> 00:40:17,268
Other than the fact that we are
not on good terms with Mr Shin,

656
00:40:17,269 --> 00:40:20,738
as a man, he is tall and good looking.

657
00:40:20,739 --> 00:40:22,558
He seems strong and manly.

658
00:40:22,559 --> 00:40:24,168
When he smiles, it's like
looking at a sunflower.

659
00:40:24,169 --> 00:40:25,618
He seems like a great guy.

660
00:40:25,619 --> 00:40:28,838
He's never been in a relationship before.

661
00:40:28,839 --> 00:40:30,698
How do you know so much about him?

662
00:40:30,699 --> 00:40:32,049
- Ms Hwang!
- What?

663
00:40:32,849 --> 00:40:35,479
Would you like me to help you out?

664
00:40:50,749 --> 00:40:51,919
What brings you here?

665
00:41:00,219 --> 00:41:01,419
I'd like...

666
00:41:03,319 --> 00:41:04,679
to defend you.

667
00:41:05,279 --> 00:41:07,319
You want to defend me?

668
00:41:08,049 --> 00:41:09,389
I'd like to give you...

669
00:41:10,519 --> 00:41:11,849
a chance to atone for your deeds.

670
00:41:13,949 --> 00:41:15,979
I already found a lawyer.

671
00:41:17,679 --> 00:41:18,749
I know.

672
00:41:20,119 --> 00:41:23,889
Will you try to prove my innocence?

673
00:41:25,389 --> 00:41:26,449
No.

674
00:41:27,819 --> 00:41:29,919
I'd like you to be...

675
00:41:30,719 --> 00:41:32,249
judged by the law...

676
00:41:33,049 --> 00:41:35,389
for the crimes you have committed.

677
00:41:38,279 --> 00:41:40,219
It's an interesting suggestion,

678
00:41:40,779 --> 00:41:41,889
but I'm going to decline.

679
00:41:48,619 --> 00:41:49,719
Mr Shin,

680
00:41:50,979 --> 00:41:52,389
take my hand.

681
00:41:55,779 --> 00:41:57,149
You offered me...

682
00:41:57,549 --> 00:41:59,389
your hand...

683
00:42:00,279 --> 00:42:02,049
when I had no money or connections.

684
00:42:03,019 --> 00:42:04,049
I think...

685
00:42:05,519 --> 00:42:07,889
it's my turn to offer you my hand.

686
00:42:11,389 --> 00:42:12,419
I was...

687
00:42:13,479 --> 00:42:15,049
going to kill you.

688
00:42:16,119 --> 00:42:17,319
That's the truth.

689
00:42:19,949 --> 00:42:22,349
I'm willing to pay for that...

690
00:42:24,119 --> 00:42:25,649
for as long as you wish.

691
00:42:28,779 --> 00:42:30,779
I really appreciate your offer.

692
00:42:31,889 --> 00:42:32,889
I do.

693
00:42:36,119 --> 00:42:37,479
Thanks for coming.

694
00:42:58,579 --> 00:43:02,049
(Trial for Shin Young Il for
bribery and inciting murder)

695
00:43:16,219 --> 00:43:17,249
Prosecution.

696
00:43:17,679 --> 00:43:19,219
State the charges.

697
00:43:39,119 --> 00:43:40,119
Defendant.

698
00:43:55,449 --> 00:43:56,779
Defendant Shin Young Il...

699
00:44:00,449 --> 00:44:02,279
abused his title as Chief Prosecutor...

700
00:44:04,279 --> 00:44:06,119
to incite the murder of Mr Joe.

701
00:44:07,479 --> 00:44:10,319
Furthermore, he accepted bribes...

702
00:44:11,719 --> 00:44:13,749
from Chairman Jung Geun
Moo of Daehwa Group.

703
00:44:16,319 --> 00:44:17,949
The prosecution charges the
defendant in accordance with...

704
00:44:18,379 --> 00:44:20,719
Article 31 of the Criminal
Code for murder instigation,

705
00:44:21,679 --> 00:44:24,019
Article 120 for bribery...

706
00:44:24,449 --> 00:44:30,579
and Article 123 for
abusing one's authority.

707
00:45:19,579 --> 00:45:20,919
Everything is over now.

708
00:45:22,479 --> 00:45:24,149
In the end, Mr Shin...

709
00:45:24,949 --> 00:45:26,879
didn't take my hand.

710
00:45:32,019 --> 00:45:34,028
You punk. You asked for this.

711
00:45:34,029 --> 00:45:35,438
Gosh, you stink!

712
00:45:35,439 --> 00:45:36,879
Let go. You smell horrible.

713
00:45:39,349 --> 00:45:40,579
Stop it!

714
00:45:46,119 --> 00:45:47,819
People don't change easily.

715
00:45:49,149 --> 00:45:50,719
When Mr Shin serves out his sentence,

716
00:45:52,019 --> 00:45:55,219
he might become a scarier monster.

717
00:45:57,249 --> 00:45:58,549
But I saw.

718
00:45:59,219 --> 00:46:01,379
I saw him struggle...

719
00:46:01,979 --> 00:46:03,879
when I offered him my hand.

720
00:46:06,379 --> 00:46:07,649
That will suffice.

721
00:46:10,019 --> 00:46:12,619
All I need is hope that the
world and the people in it...

722
00:46:13,549 --> 00:46:15,149
can change.

723
00:46:17,349 --> 00:46:18,449
That is the reason why...

724
00:46:19,319 --> 00:46:20,649
I live on...

725
00:46:21,649 --> 00:46:23,019
as a neighborhood lawyer.

726
00:46:30,779 --> 00:46:33,279
(One year later)

727
00:46:35,319 --> 00:46:40,119
(Court Room 305)

728
00:46:41,249 --> 00:46:43,688
Plaintiff, you were wrongfully
dismissed without...

729
00:46:43,689 --> 00:46:45,679
- any reason, correct?
- Yes.

730
00:46:46,149 --> 00:46:49,019
Please tell us how the company treated you.

731
00:46:49,519 --> 00:46:51,379
It started from petty little things.

732
00:46:51,819 --> 00:46:53,648
First, they bullied me.

733
00:46:53,649 --> 00:46:55,769
Then, they threatened me to
turn in my vacation days.

734
00:46:56,549 --> 00:46:59,749
When I complained, they hired a
new employee and moved my desk.

735
00:47:00,149 --> 00:47:01,469
Where did they move your desk to?

736
00:47:01,949 --> 00:47:03,419
Beside the water purifier.

737
00:47:04,819 --> 00:47:07,549
Everyone must have looked
at you while passing by.

738
00:47:08,179 --> 00:47:09,519
Everyone laughed at me.

739
00:47:11,649 --> 00:47:12,749
Your Honour,

740
00:47:13,549 --> 00:47:15,418
the plaintiff has been...

741
00:47:15,419 --> 00:47:17,649
a loyal employee for the past seven years.

742
00:47:18,019 --> 00:47:19,448
She was wrongfully dismissed...

743
00:47:19,449 --> 00:47:23,479
from her company for one reason.

744
00:47:24,119 --> 00:47:27,019
It was because she applied
for maternity leave.

745
00:47:27,919 --> 00:47:31,649
The labour law states everyone has
the right to take maternity leave.

746
00:47:32,119 --> 00:47:35,279
Nonetheless, the plaintiff was dismissed...

747
00:47:35,619 --> 00:47:37,279
without a proper reason.

748
00:47:38,879 --> 00:47:40,179
Does that mean...

749
00:47:40,779 --> 00:47:42,979
that she shouldn't have given
birth in the first place?

750
00:47:45,119 --> 00:47:47,379
I request your wise decision.

751
00:47:48,349 --> 00:47:50,379
No more questions.

752
00:48:01,849 --> 00:48:02,849
Ms Lee.

753
00:48:04,319 --> 00:48:06,519
You were impressive today.

754
00:48:07,779 --> 00:48:09,319
Thank you for the compliment.

755
00:48:09,849 --> 00:48:11,719
My client wants to settle.

756
00:48:12,049 --> 00:48:13,049
What do you say?

757
00:48:13,749 --> 00:48:15,979
If the conditions are
right, we'll consider.

758
00:48:17,749 --> 00:48:21,318
Mr Joe, the other party asked to settle.

759
00:48:21,319 --> 00:48:22,588
Settle?

760
00:48:22,589 --> 00:48:24,949
That's great. We won't need
to continue with the trial.

761
00:48:25,479 --> 00:48:27,128
I'm heading to Geum San.

762
00:48:27,129 --> 00:48:28,579
You should head over, too.

763
00:48:29,679 --> 00:48:31,049
You take care of it.

764
00:48:31,849 --> 00:48:32,849
Me?

765
00:48:33,319 --> 00:48:35,319
Do you want me to decide
on the settlement amount?

766
00:48:35,819 --> 00:48:37,118
You don't want to?

767
00:48:37,119 --> 00:48:39,219
No, it's not that I don't want to...

768
00:48:41,219 --> 00:48:43,028
You can't complain later.

769
00:48:43,029 --> 00:48:44,538
You can't nag and complain...

770
00:48:44,539 --> 00:48:47,148
that I didn't ask for more, or that
the conditions aren't good enough.

771
00:48:47,149 --> 00:48:49,028
I'm not a nag.

772
00:48:49,029 --> 00:48:52,049
This case is yours, so you finish it.

773
00:48:52,419 --> 00:48:54,319
You're sure, right? This is my case, right?

774
00:48:54,679 --> 00:48:55,679
That's what I said.

775
00:48:56,479 --> 00:48:59,519
Then naturally, I should decide.

776
00:49:00,779 --> 00:49:01,779
Yes.

777
00:49:11,819 --> 00:49:12,819
Okay.

778
00:49:13,249 --> 00:49:14,249
Let's proceed with this.

779
00:49:16,579 --> 00:49:19,949
Ms Lee. You've become a
real pro in just a year.

780
00:49:20,879 --> 00:49:22,479
It's all thanks to Mr Joe.

781
00:49:23,149 --> 00:49:25,968
I've experienced all sorts of battles...

782
00:49:25,969 --> 00:49:27,449
while working with him.

783
00:49:28,619 --> 00:49:29,779
It must be fun.

784
00:49:30,249 --> 00:49:31,368
Pardon?

785
00:49:31,369 --> 00:49:34,479
So much that it doesn't compare
with your time here at Geum San.

786
00:49:35,279 --> 00:49:37,779
Yes. That's true.

787
00:49:38,719 --> 00:49:40,728
How are things in your office?

788
00:49:40,729 --> 00:49:42,519
We're swamped as usual.

789
00:49:42,979 --> 00:49:45,549
He's so famous in the area as you know.

790
00:49:45,919 --> 00:49:47,738
What are you doing? No, no.

791
00:49:47,739 --> 00:49:49,008
- That's not right.
- Come on.

792
00:49:49,009 --> 00:49:50,758
It's almost done.

793
00:49:50,759 --> 00:49:52,538
Word got out that consultations are free,

794
00:49:52,539 --> 00:49:54,219
so people come from afar, too.

795
00:49:54,849 --> 00:49:56,918
If you search online,

796
00:49:56,919 --> 00:49:58,959
it also shows up as "Free
consultation law office".

797
00:49:59,549 --> 00:50:00,968
Are you getting paid regularly?

798
00:50:00,969 --> 00:50:02,019
Of course.

799
00:50:02,349 --> 00:50:04,069
At least I don't have to work odd jobs now.

800
00:50:05,119 --> 00:50:07,479
How's Ms Hwang doing?

801
00:50:10,579 --> 00:50:12,918
Get what? A divorce?

802
00:50:12,919 --> 00:50:15,158
Why didn't you do anything...

803
00:50:15,159 --> 00:50:17,368
when I said I was getting married?

804
00:50:17,369 --> 00:50:19,108
You should've stopped me.

805
00:50:19,109 --> 00:50:20,868
You were so in love.

806
00:50:20,869 --> 00:50:22,738
You said you had to get married
because you were pregnant.

807
00:50:22,739 --> 00:50:23,838
Did I?

808
00:50:23,839 --> 00:50:25,848
I must have had lost my mind.

809
00:50:25,849 --> 00:50:27,708
I can't live with him.

810
00:50:27,709 --> 00:50:29,408
My gosh. I'm going crazy.

811
00:50:29,409 --> 00:50:31,238
Why are you fighting?

812
00:50:31,239 --> 00:50:32,908
Our personalities and everything clash.

813
00:50:32,909 --> 00:50:34,568
We're too different.

814
00:50:34,569 --> 00:50:35,638
What about the baby?

815
00:50:35,639 --> 00:50:38,468
I'm taking custody of my baby.

816
00:50:38,469 --> 00:50:39,568
Not a chance!

817
00:50:39,569 --> 00:50:41,198
Over my dead body.

818
00:50:41,199 --> 00:50:43,338
Mr Joe, divorce is one thing,

819
00:50:43,339 --> 00:50:46,108
but I need to have full
custody over the baby.

820
00:50:46,109 --> 00:50:48,158
Have you lost your mind?

821
00:50:48,159 --> 00:50:50,038
- Yes, I have!
- It's in my belly.

822
00:50:50,039 --> 00:50:52,628
I won't give you a cent in alimony.

823
00:50:52,629 --> 00:50:55,008
- You have to give her half.
- Right.

824
00:50:55,009 --> 00:50:57,638
I earned all of that before we got married.

825
00:50:57,639 --> 00:50:59,468
- It doesn't matter.
- Mr Joe.

826
00:50:59,469 --> 00:51:00,838
You'll represent me, right?

827
00:51:00,839 --> 00:51:02,768
He's my lawyer.

828
00:51:02,769 --> 00:51:04,138
I worked with him longer.

829
00:51:04,139 --> 00:51:05,868
We're like brothers.

830
00:51:05,869 --> 00:51:07,238
He's closer than my real brother!

831
00:51:07,239 --> 00:51:10,168
See? She's always starting up with me.

832
00:51:10,169 --> 00:51:12,138
She's always starting fights.

833
00:51:12,139 --> 00:51:14,468
You have no right to say that!

834
00:51:14,469 --> 00:51:16,038
Why don't I?

835
00:51:16,039 --> 00:51:19,108
Have you once cooked for
me since we got married?

836
00:51:19,109 --> 00:51:22,349
You always feed me instant noodles.
That's not a decent meal.

837
00:51:23,049 --> 00:51:24,149
- Hey.
- Noodles?

838
00:51:24,819 --> 00:51:26,538
Why are you picking on noodles?

839
00:51:26,539 --> 00:51:27,968
I don't believe this.

840
00:51:27,969 --> 00:51:30,708
You said you love noodles so much
that you could eat them every day.

841
00:51:30,709 --> 00:51:33,268
- When did I say that?
- You said my love is all you need.

842
00:51:33,269 --> 00:51:35,598
And that woman!

843
00:51:35,599 --> 00:51:37,698
Ask that woman to cook for you.

844
00:51:37,699 --> 00:51:39,938
He has another woman.

845
00:51:39,939 --> 00:51:41,568
- Do you have another woman?
- It's a misunderstanding.

846
00:51:41,569 --> 00:51:42,908
She's a childhood friend.

847
00:51:42,909 --> 00:51:45,338
Who texts their childhood
friend every day and giggles?

848
00:51:45,339 --> 00:51:47,938
- It wasn't every day. It was once.
- It was every day.

849
00:51:47,939 --> 00:51:50,638
- You giggled?
- No, I wrote "laughing out loud".

850
00:51:50,639 --> 00:51:53,748
- Don't lie.
- Forget it!

851
00:51:53,749 --> 00:51:54,868
Goodness.

852
00:51:54,869 --> 00:51:56,208
Fine! Let's get a divorce!

853
00:51:56,209 --> 00:51:57,468
Get a divorce.

854
00:51:57,469 --> 00:52:00,018
What?

855
00:52:00,019 --> 00:52:03,108
Split your assets down the middle,

856
00:52:03,109 --> 00:52:05,538
and cut the baby in half, too.

857
00:52:05,539 --> 00:52:07,488
I misjudged you.

858
00:52:07,489 --> 00:52:09,468
- How could you say that?
- What?

859
00:52:09,469 --> 00:52:11,138
How could you say that?

860
00:52:11,139 --> 00:52:12,468
That's what you do when you get a divorce.

861
00:52:12,469 --> 00:52:14,438
I'm so disappointed.

862
00:52:14,439 --> 00:52:16,538
How could you say that?

863
00:52:16,539 --> 00:52:18,049
I'd do the same even if it were me.

864
00:52:19,279 --> 00:52:20,968
Oh my gosh.

865
00:52:20,969 --> 00:52:23,718
What's wrong? What... What's wrong?

866
00:52:23,719 --> 00:52:26,179
What's wrong? Is it the baby?

867
00:52:27,049 --> 00:52:28,379
It's coming.

868
00:52:29,879 --> 00:52:32,308
- How can you cut the baby in half?
- Come here.

869
00:52:32,309 --> 00:52:33,808
- Are you having your baby?
- We'll be back.

870
00:52:33,809 --> 00:52:35,968
- It's your fault!
- Okay, okay.

871
00:52:35,969 --> 00:52:37,138
Is she having her baby?

872
00:52:37,139 --> 00:52:38,808
I think so.

873
00:52:38,809 --> 00:52:39,968
I'm having my baby.

874
00:52:39,969 --> 00:52:41,508
Hold on.

875
00:52:41,509 --> 00:52:42,519
Wait.

876
00:52:43,679 --> 00:52:45,249
Are you serious?

877
00:52:46,579 --> 00:52:47,579
Are you?

878
00:52:55,979 --> 00:52:56,979
Hi, Jin Young.

879
00:52:57,979 --> 00:52:59,259
Where else would I be? I'm home.

880
00:53:00,449 --> 00:53:01,619
Beer?

881
00:53:02,419 --> 00:53:03,649
You should've called sooner.

882
00:53:05,379 --> 00:53:08,519
Okay, okay. I'm coming.

883
00:53:11,579 --> 00:53:13,019
Where is she?

884
00:53:19,379 --> 00:53:20,438
Ms Lee?

885
00:53:20,439 --> 00:53:21,519
Mr Shin.

886
00:53:21,849 --> 00:53:22,849
Hello.

887
00:53:25,879 --> 00:53:28,028
Are you meeting someone here?

888
00:53:28,029 --> 00:53:30,708
Yes. What about you?

889
00:53:30,709 --> 00:53:33,249
Yes. I'm meeting a fellow lawyer friend.

890
00:53:33,579 --> 00:53:34,818
And you?

891
00:53:34,819 --> 00:53:36,319
I... Well...

892
00:53:36,979 --> 00:53:40,219
Seeing how you can't answer me
makes me think it's a blind date.

893
00:53:41,049 --> 00:53:42,108
Yes.

894
00:53:42,109 --> 00:53:43,179
Who set it up?

895
00:53:44,179 --> 00:53:45,179
A lawyer friend...

896
00:53:47,119 --> 00:53:48,759
- The public defender...
- Oh Jin Young?

897
00:53:51,579 --> 00:53:52,649
Goodness.

898
00:53:54,749 --> 00:53:55,749
Soo Bin.

899
00:53:56,179 --> 00:53:57,179
- Daddy's here.
- Daddy!

900
00:53:57,549 --> 00:54:00,149
You look so pretty.

901
00:54:01,579 --> 00:54:03,498
You look like a princess.

902
00:54:03,499 --> 00:54:05,038
It smells great.

903
00:54:05,039 --> 00:54:07,198
- Hi.
- It smells great.

904
00:54:07,199 --> 00:54:08,249
I made kimchi stew.

905
00:54:08,919 --> 00:54:10,708
Did Mummy make all of this?

906
00:54:10,709 --> 00:54:11,768
Yes.

907
00:54:11,769 --> 00:54:13,708
Really? Wow. I'm impressed.

908
00:54:13,709 --> 00:54:15,038
Actually, we bought it.

909
00:54:15,039 --> 00:54:16,608
See? I knew it.

910
00:54:16,609 --> 00:54:17,758
Hey.

911
00:54:17,759 --> 00:54:18,949
Soo Bin. Here.

912
00:54:19,679 --> 00:54:21,819
- Ta-da!
- It looks like you.

913
00:54:23,619 --> 00:54:24,818
It tastes good.

914
00:54:24,819 --> 00:54:25,879
It's spicy.

915
00:54:26,279 --> 00:54:29,808
- Front legs out, hind legs out
- Front legs out, hind legs out

916
00:54:29,809 --> 00:54:33,049
- Leaping, leaping, it became a frog
- Leaping, leaping, it became a frog

917
00:54:43,479 --> 00:54:46,719
The law is not fair to everyone.

918
00:54:48,479 --> 00:54:52,449
It is a time for solitude
and reflection for some.

919
00:54:58,679 --> 00:54:59,679
Hi.

920
00:55:00,379 --> 00:55:01,379
Goodness.

921
00:55:02,119 --> 00:55:03,619
Thanks. Sit.

922
00:55:07,379 --> 00:55:08,379
How have you been?

923
00:55:09,479 --> 00:55:10,479
I've been well.

924
00:55:10,949 --> 00:55:13,308
- Is everything okay?
- To some people's families,

925
00:55:13,309 --> 00:55:14,838
You can't get sick, okay?

926
00:55:14,839 --> 00:55:16,819
It can be a painful wait.

927
00:55:18,519 --> 00:55:19,848
Some have...

928
00:55:19,849 --> 00:55:22,819
a personal lawyer who
visits them every day.

929
00:55:24,519 --> 00:55:27,779
Of course, you must pay a very high fee.

930
00:55:32,449 --> 00:55:33,819
We recommend...

931
00:55:34,179 --> 00:55:35,749
one year in prison.

932
00:55:36,449 --> 00:55:38,479
Defense, make your closing statement.

933
00:55:42,119 --> 00:55:43,119
And here,

934
00:55:43,819 --> 00:55:45,779
there is a person who was detained...

935
00:55:46,249 --> 00:55:47,719
for stealing an eight-dollar candy.

936
00:55:48,379 --> 00:55:49,519
Your Honour,

937
00:55:51,049 --> 00:55:52,049
the defendant is here...

938
00:55:52,719 --> 00:55:54,679
on a charge of theft.

939
00:55:55,449 --> 00:55:57,119
She stole one bag of candy...

940
00:55:58,049 --> 00:55:59,619
from a local supermarket.

941
00:56:00,549 --> 00:56:02,119
The cost of that bag of candy...

942
00:56:03,279 --> 00:56:04,279
is eight dollars.

943
00:56:05,349 --> 00:56:06,549
Because of that eight dollars,

944
00:56:06,979 --> 00:56:09,679
the owner handed her over to the police,

945
00:56:10,149 --> 00:56:12,748
and the police sent her to
the prosecutor because...

946
00:56:12,749 --> 00:56:13,919
it was not her first offense.

947
00:56:16,279 --> 00:56:18,179
The defendant stole the
same bag of candy...

948
00:56:18,649 --> 00:56:20,679
from the same supermarket three times.

949
00:56:21,949 --> 00:56:27,428
The total price of candy that she
stole thus far is 24 dollars.

950
00:56:27,429 --> 00:56:30,238
The wholesale price of the candy...

951
00:56:30,239 --> 00:56:32,188
is half of that,

952
00:56:32,189 --> 00:56:33,449
which is 12 dollars.

953
00:56:33,949 --> 00:56:36,228
Defendant is being detained
at a detention centre...

954
00:56:36,229 --> 00:56:37,979
for 24 dollars.

955
00:56:39,379 --> 00:56:42,238
It was wrong to steal the candy...

956
00:56:42,239 --> 00:56:43,449
I am a neighbourhood lawyer.

957
00:56:44,419 --> 00:56:46,279
Most consultations are free,

958
00:56:46,849 --> 00:56:48,528
and no matter how small the case,

959
00:56:48,529 --> 00:56:50,318
if the client was wronged,

960
00:56:50,319 --> 00:56:52,419
I defend them regardless of the fee.

961
00:56:54,119 --> 00:56:55,649
I am not a warrior of justice.

962
00:56:57,379 --> 00:56:59,148
I am not Superman,

963
00:56:59,149 --> 00:57:00,519
as Soo Bin thinks.

964
00:57:01,949 --> 00:57:02,949
However,

965
00:57:03,279 --> 00:57:04,649
if I see someone who is wronged,

966
00:57:05,419 --> 00:57:06,819
I can't just walk on by.

967
00:57:09,679 --> 00:57:10,679
As long as...

968
00:57:11,349 --> 00:57:14,149
there are people who are wronged in
my neighbourhood and in this land,

969
00:57:15,819 --> 00:57:18,319
I will continue to do my job.

970
00:57:19,749 --> 00:57:21,879
Regardless of how petty the crime,

971
00:57:22,349 --> 00:57:24,668
the punishment was escalated...

972
00:57:24,669 --> 00:57:26,918
because it was her third offense.

973
00:57:26,919 --> 00:57:28,779
Don't you think this is wrong?

974
00:57:51,549 --> 00:57:55,019
(My Lawyer, Mr Joe)

